                        <support>1 papyrus ; 11.5 x 8 cm.</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">This light-brown papyrus is complete. Worm holes are scattered throughout the document, especially in lines 2,3, and 6, causing some difficulty in reading. A pattern of vertical holes evident proportionately on both left and right sides of the document suggests perhaps its shape when found: folded horizontally. Two large holes on the right side of lines 2 and 3,a nd two others equal in size on the left side of line 6 supports such a pattern.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">1-7</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The hand, being a fairly rapid cursive, varies in size and texture throughout. There is severe compression of letters, particularly at the end of line 5 and much of line 6. The greater part of line 6 is faded or lost. The left side suggests an irregular margin slanting outward. The top of the papyrus has 1 cm. blank and the bottom part 2.5 cm. blank.</p>
